# C# → JavaScript Core

## Types & Conversions

| C# | JavaScript / TypeScript |
|----|-------------------------|
| `int`, `double`, `bool` | `number`, `boolean` (no separate int type) |
| `string` | `string` |
| `null` | `null` **and** `undefined` (two "empty" values) |
| `var x = ...` (inferred) | `let x = ...` or `const x = ...` |
| `const` / `readonly` | `const` (objects still mutable; binding is frozen) |
| `(int)s` cast | `Number(s)`, `parseInt(s, 10)`, `String(n)` |
| `Convert.ToInt32(s)` | `parseInt(s, 10)` or `Number(s)` |
| `x?.Prop` | `x?.prop` (same optional chaining) |
| `x ?? default` | `x ?? default` (same nullish coalescing) |

**Strict equality:** always prefer `===` / `!==` (C# `==` is closer to `===`, not `==`).

## Classes & OOP

| C# | JS/TS |
|----|-------|
| `class Foo : Bar` | `class Foo extends Bar` |
| `public` (default) | no keyword needed |
| `private` field | `#field` (private) or `private field` in TS |
| Constructor | `constructor(...) { }` |
| `interface IFoo` | `interface IFoo` (TS only; erased at runtime) |
| `record` / init-only | plain object + `as const` or TS `readonly` |
| `static` | `static` (same) |
| `async Task<T>` | `async function(): Promise<T>` |

## Modules (not namespaces)

- C#: `namespace` + `using` → JS: `import` / `export` (ESM) or `require` (CJS).
- Prefer **ESM** (`import`/`export`) in new code; Node supports it via `"type": "module"` in `package.json`.
- No `using` aliases — use named imports: `import { foo } from './foo.js'`.

## Async

| C# | JS/TS |
|----|-------|
| `async Task` | `async function` → returns `Promise<void>` |
| `await x` | `await x` (same syntax) |
| `Task.WhenAll` | `Promise.all([...])` |
| `Task.WhenAny` | `Promise.race([...])` |
| `CancellationToken` | `AbortController` + `signal` |

## Collections

| C# | JS/TS |
|----|-------|
| `List<T>` | `T[]` or `Array<T>` |
| `Dictionary<K,V>` | `Map<K,V>` or plain `Record<K,V>` / `{ [key: string]: V }` |
| `HashSet<T>` | `Set<T>` |
| LINQ `.Where().Select()` | `.filter().map()` |
| `foreach` | `for (const x of arr)` |
